Import_1Password_Instructions_Mac.message:
Open 1Password and log in.
While logged into your 1Password account, click the "File" dropdown menu in the upper left corner of your Menu Bar. Select "Export" and then click the "All Items..." option.
You will be prompted to confirm that you would like to export by entering your Master Password. Enter it and click the blue "Continue" button.
The "Save As" menu will pop up. Name the file, choose its location, and ensure that you select "Comma Delimited Text (.csv)" from the "File Format" dropdown menu. Under "Fields to Export" you will need to check the box labeled "Include Common Labels" otherwise importing to RoboForm will fail. When you have ensured that your export settings are correct, click the blue "Save" button.

Import_1Password_Instructions_Win.message:
Open 1Password and log in.
Select the data you wish to export. You can select multiple data objects by holding down the Shift or Ctrl keys while clicking on them. You can also mass select all of the saved data by pressing "Ctrl + A" after clicking one of the items in the list. After selecting the items you wish to export, right-click the selected data and choose "Export" from the menu which will appear.
You will be prompted to confirm that you would like to export by entering your Master Password. Enter it and click the "Export" button.
The "Save As" menu will pop up. Ensure that you select Comma-separated values (CSV) from the "Save as type" dropdown menu, then name the file, note its location, and click "Save."

Import_Bitwarden_Instructions.message:
Open your browser and log in to your Bitwarden account. Click "Tools" in the upper left.
Select "Export Vault" from the column on the left. Under "File Format" select the option for a .csv file. Enter your Master Password. Then, click the blue "Export Vault" button.
You will be prompted to confirm the export, click the blue "Export Vault" button on this prompt. Bitwarden will export a CSV file titled "bitwarden_export_##############.csv" into your designated downloads folder.

Import_Chrome_Instructions.message:
Open Chrome and click the 3 vertical dots in the upper right corner. Select "Settings" from the menu.
Click "Passwords" under the Autofill section of the Settings menu. To the right of "Saved Passwords" click the 3 vertical dots. Click the "Export passwords..." option.
A window will appear prompting you to confirm the export, click the blue "Export passwords..." button. The "Save As" dialogue will appear. Name the CSV file and choose its location.

Import_Dashlane_Instructions.message:
Open your browser and click the Dashlane extension.
Click the "More" button in the upper right of the extension's menu and select the "Open the app" option.
Click "My Account" in the lower left corner and select "Export Data" from the menu that appears. Enter your Master Password and then click the "Export to CSV" option.
A .zip file containing your Dashlane data will download to your designated downloads folder. Unzip the folder and you will see five different CSV files. The CSV which contains your login credentials is the one labeled "credentials.csv"

Import_Edge_Instructions.message:
Open Edge and click the 3 dots in the upper right corner. Select "Settings" from the menu.
Select "Profiles" from the column on the left and then click the "Passwords" option. To the right of "Saved Passwords" click the 3 dots. Click the "Export passwords" option.
A window will appear prompting you to confirm the export, click the blue "Export passwords" button. On the next prompt, input your User Password and click the "OK" button to initiate the export. The "Save As" dialogue will appear. Name the CSV file and choose its location.

Import_Enpass_Instructions_Mac.message:
Open Enpass and log in. Click the "File" dropdown menu in the upper left, then select "Export".
The export dialogue will open on the right. Under "Select Format of File" select ".json" format. Then, click the "Folder" icon under "Choose Location" to select the destination for the export. Name the file as you wish, and click the "Save" button at the bottom of the screen.
Click the export button. You will be prompted to input your Master Password to confirm this action. Input the password and click confirm. Enpass will confirm that your export was successful. Click the "Done" button.

Import_Enpass_Instructions_Win.message:
Open Enpass and log in. Click the 3 stacked horizontal lines in the upper right corner, select "File," and then click the "Export" option.
The export dialogue will open on the right. Under "Select Format of File" select ".json" format. Then, click the "Folder" icon under "Choose Location" to select the destination for the export. Name the file as you wish, and click the "Save" button at the bottom of the screen.
Click the export button. You will be prompted to input your Master Password to confirm this action. Input the password and click confirm. Enpass will confirm that your export was successful. Click the "Done" button.

Import_Firefox_Instructions.message:
Open Firefox and click the 3 horizontal lines in the upper right corner. Select "Passwords" from the menu.
At the top right corner of the Logins and Passwords page, click the 3 dots. Select "Export Logins..." from the menu. You will receive a message prompting you to confirm that you would like to export. Click the red "Export..." button.
The "Save As" dialogue will appear. Name the CSV file and choose its location.

Import_Keeper_Instructions_Mac.message:
Open Keeper and go to your Vault.
Click the account dropdown menu in the upper right corner and select the "Settings" option. Select "Export" from the column on the left.
To the right of "Export to .csv File" click the "Export Now" button. You will then be prompted to enter your Master Password. Enter it, and click the yellow "Export Now" button.
The "Save As" menu will pop up. Name the file, choose its location, and click "Save." Keeper will export a CSV file containing your data into your designated downloads folder.

Import_Keeper_Instructions_Win.message:
Open Keeper and go to your Vault.
Click the account dropdown menu in the upper right corner and select the "Settings" option. Select "Export" from the column on the left.
To the right of "Export to .csv File" click the "Export Now" button. You will then be prompted to enter your Master Password. Enter it, and click the yellow "Export Now" button.
Keeper will export a CSV file containing your data into your designated downloads folder.

Import_LastPass_Instructions.message:
In your web browser toolbar, click the LastPass icon then click "Open My Vault". Select "Advanced Options" in the left navigation section at the bottom.
Click the "Export" option. If prompted, enter your Master Password and click the red "Continue" button.
LastPass will export a CSV file titled "lastpass_export.csv" into your designated downloads folder.

Import_Last_Instruction.message: Once done, click "Import from file" below.

Import_NordPass_Instructions.message:
Open the NordPass desktop app and log in to your account. Click the Settings (gear) icon in the upper left.
Scroll down to the "Import and Export" section and select the "Export Items" option. You will be prompted to enter your Master Password to confirm the export.
The "Save As" dialogue will appear. Name the CSV file and choose its location. Then, click the "Save" button.

Import_Opera_Instructions.message:
Open Opera and click Opera icon in the upper left corner. Select "Settings" from the menu.
Click "Passwords" under the Autofill section. To the right of "Saved Passwords" click the 3 vertical dots. Click the "Export passwords..." option.
A window will appear prompting you to confirm the export, click the blue "Export passwords..." button. The "Save As" dialogue will appear. Name the CSV file and choose its location.

Import_TrueKey_Instructions.message:
Log in to True Key and click the "Gear" icon in the upper right hand corner. Then, click the "App Settings" tab in the upper right hand corner.
Click the "Export" button to the right of the "Export Data" section. You will be presented with a window asking you to confirm this action. Click the blue "Continue" button.
You will be prompted to enter your Master Password. Enter it, and click the blue "Unlock" button. Your data will then be downloaded to your designated downloads folder.
